stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource photon science seminar series stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource an office of science user facility seminar series home about the seminar series attending a lecture past lectures maps & directions home photon science seminar series slac's new photon science seminar series brings together scientists from slac's linac coherent light source stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource photon science and accelerator directorates including researchers from the center for sustainable energy through catalysis and two joint slac stanford institutes the stanford institute for materials and energy science and the pulse institute for ultrafast energy science the seminar series main goals are to stimulate scientific exchange within the photon science community at slac and to make people aware of both the science that's underway using the ssrl and lcls machines and the capabilities they offer in particular the series seeks to present results carried out in photon science at slac at a level of technicality accessible to researchers across the various directorates and institutes the lectures take place every wednesday at 3 00 pm in slac's building 901 redtail hawk conference room every presentation will be preceded by 15 minutes of informal discussion over cookies and coffee and will be followed by time for anyone in the audience to share recent results or exciting experimental techniques speakers are invited by three representatives one from each of the ssrl lcls and photon science directorates joy hayter ssrl marvin seibert lcls brian mcfarland photon science please contact these representatives if you would like to suggest a speaker for the series if you have other questions about the series please contact samira baradaran share printer friendly version send to friend send to friend the stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource is a directorate of slac national accelerator laboratory which is operated by stanford university for 